<br>
<font color=red>My thoughts</font>: <br>
<br>
<font color=Blue>NEW UBER WEAPONS!</font> Nuff said,  lets get to finding these!<br>
<br>
<font color=Blue>Mark of Karn</font>:   Man,  that really blows.  For those of you not familiar with Mark of Karn, it is a Cleric only spell, that casts an inverse damage shield on the target creature. Each time somone hit that creature, health was restored to them at 10hp per hit.  <br>
<br>
Verant decided to downgrade this spell quite a bit in the most recent patch. The recast delay is 5 minutes now(used to be 5secs), thus it will not be used in every fight, unless pulls are very slow. Also, they decreased the amount of healing done per swing to 6 hps. (Note: This spell is heavily resisted, and if so, a resist also restarts that 5 minute recast delay.)<br>
<br>
In most cases, a Cleric will use Complete Heal to keep any tank-types (War/SK/Pal) healthy. Many of us don't like having to repeatedly heal the melee damage dealers such as Rogues, Monks and Rangers. MoK was able to help in this regard, because it would cover most of the healing for a few hits here and there. <br>
<br>
Pre-Nerf, It wouldn't keep someone healed if a creature is glued to one of the damage dealers (Rog/Mnk/Rng) through the whole fight, but it does keep these classes from being a severe mana-sink at all times.<br>
<br>
I fear that this change to MoK is going to hurt all the high level players in EQ, by making Cleric downtime MUCH worse, and by making Melee/Hybrid damage dealers more of a liability to a group when they get aggroed.<br>
<br>
<font color=Blue>Blacksmithing and Dyes</font>:  Very cool,  have to start doing some of this stuff.<br>
<br>
<font color=Blue>Base Dmg Decrease in Low Delay 2H Weaps</font> Nerf!  This one has to suck for Monks with good 2H Blunt weapons and Warriors.  =(<br>
<br>
<font color=Blue>My Outlook on this patch</font>:   Some very Good stuff,  adn some bad stuff.  I think VI waited so long for this patch so they could get the Uber Weapons in.  Think about it,  everyone will be trying to get these new Uber weapons or tryiong to raise Blacksmithing instead of ranting about these Nerfs.  But the Nerfs do out number the Good things.  I cant wait until VI will stop tweaking stuff and let us play the damn game.<br>
<br>
